"```sql\nSELECT CONCAT(d.forename, ' ', d.surname) AS full_name\nFROM drivers d\nJOIN pitStops ps ON d.driverId = ps.driverId\nWHERE d.nationality = 'German'\n  AND d.dob > '1980-01-01'\n  AND d.dob < '1985-12-31'\nGROUP BY d.driverId\nORDER BY AVG(ps.duration) ASC\nLIMIT 3;\n```\n\nThis SQL query selects the full names of the top 3 German drivers with the shortest average pit stop duration, who were born between 1980 and 1985. It joins the `drivers` and `pitStops` tables on `driverId`, filters for German nationality and the specified birth date range, groups by driver, and orders by the average pit stop duration in ascending order, limiting the results to the top 3."